title: Pakistani cricket team in England in 2006

tables.PakistanPakistan Test Squad, from Cricin: Pakistan [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/squad/249959.html Pakistan Test Squad] , from Cricinfo, retrieved 31 July 2006

Naved-ul-Hasan withdrew before the series started, and was replaced by Samiullah Khan Niazi. He returned to the squad for the fourth Test, but was not selected. [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/story/256548.html Hafeez to open as Shoaib is ruled out] , by Andrew Miller, Cricinfo, retrieved 18 August 2006 On 15 July, Mohammad Asif and Shoaib Malik returned home, and were replaced by Iftikhar Anjum and Taufeeq Umar. Iftikhar Anjum left several days later following his father's death, with no replacement called up. [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/story/254387.html Rao Iftikhar leaves squad after father's death] , from Cricinfo, retrieved 31 July 2006 Salman Butt, Samiullah Khan Niazi and Taufeeq Umar travelled home before the fourth Test, and Mohammad Hafeez was called up. Faisal Iqbal, Mohammad Sami and Shahid Nazir returned home after the Test series, and were replaced by Shahid Yousuf and Shoaib Malik. [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/squad/257034.html Pakistan One-Day Squad] , from Cricinfo, retrieved 24 August 2006 Mohammad Asif and Shoaib Akhtar only played in the ODI series, having returned from injury.

England [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/squad/252784.html England Squad – 1st Test] , retrieved from Cricinfo 31 July 2006 [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/squad/254245.html England Squad – 2nd Test] , retrieved from Cricinfo 31 July 2006

Dalrymple was only selected for the second Test, and later withdrawn along with Plunkett as the squad was cut down from 14 to 12. 
Read was added for the third Test after Jones suffered a finger injury, though the English chairman of selectors said that "the decision was taken regardless of the injury to Geraint's finger" [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/current/story/255067.html Read called up as England drop Jones] , from Cricinfo, retrieved 31 July 2006 He also played the fourth Test.

Broad, Clarke, Gough, Joyce and Yardy were only selected for the ODI squad. Hoggard and Panesar were only selected for the Test squad. [http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/current/story/257602.html Gough and Broad in England squad] , from Cricinfo, retrieved 24 August 2006 Gough withdrew after the second ODI with a shin injury, and Onions was called up to replace him. [http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/cricket/england/5310512.stm Injured Gough replaced by Onions] , from BBC, retrieved 4 September 2006

tables.Winner: KOR USA Sukjin-Lee Wuesthoff   Wuesthoff moved from her native South Korea to New Jersey as a 12-year-old, moving in and eventually being adopted by an American aunt and uncle. When the Child Citizenship Act of 2000 took effect on February 27, 2001, she automatically acquired United States citizenship, as she was legally adopted by at least one American citizen and was under 18 on the effective date of the Act. However, when she joined the LPGA tour in 2008, the tour listed her as South Korean, indicating that she retained her original citizenship.

tables.ADVANCEMENT: Upgrading from category 5 to 4 can be done after finishing ten mass start races. Category 4 to 3 can be requested when a certain number of points are earned in races within a 12-month period or race experience, 25 qualifying races with a minimum of 10 top ten finishes with fields of 30 riders or more. 30 points in a 12-month period is an automatic upgrade to category 3. Upgrades from 3 to 2 and 2 to 1 are based on a number of points in a 12-month period. Category 3 to 2 requires 25 points to be eligible and 40 points for an automatic upgrade.

Upgrading in cyclo-cross follows the same upgrade pattern as road but with different points requirements. In this case it is 10 points in a 12-month period to upgrade from category 3 to 2 and 20 points from category 2 to 1.
Upgrading from track category 5 to 4 is done by taking a velodrome safety course or 4 race days, and as with road, is done by points with the added requirement of 5 race days.

Riders may upgrade to category 2 as fast as they want. After 5 top-5 finishes as a category 3 rider, a rider must upgrade to category 2. After 2 top-5 category 2 finishes, a rider may upgrade to category 1, and after 5 top-5 finishes a rider must upgrade to category 1.
